_2530226\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nek1665702923991.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nek1665702923991.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nek1665702923991.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"nek1665702923991\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                    \n Freeing Memory\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can use memory efficiently by using appropriate component implementation techniques and configuring the application and servers appropriately. Using handles allows Uniface to help with automatic garbage collection.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d734374e56\">\n                     \n Component Implementation\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nek1665702923991__p_d46379e1_d46380e1_d46381e1\">When constructing components, consider the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nek1665702923991__li_d23099e1_d23100e1_d23101e1\">Drop forms from memory as soon as they are no longer required\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nek1665702923991__li_d23102e1_d23103e1_d23104e1\">Delete instances of services that are no longer needed\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nek1665702923991__li_d23105e1_d23106e1_d23107e1\">Use limited forms with their reduced field lists\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nek1665702923991__li_d23108e1_d23109e1_d23110e1\">Clear entities as soon as the hitlist is no longer needed\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nek1665702923991__li_d23111e1_d23112e1_d23113e1\">Free cursors and locks as soon as they are no longer required\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nek1665702923991__p_d46382e1_d46383e1_d46384e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rip1665702922090.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rip1665702922090.html\" title=\"Even with an optimized application model, there are still design and implementation decisions that can affect performance, such as your choice of components, data retrieval implementation, component data structure and indexing decisions.\">Performance Guidelines for Component Logic and Implementation</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d734374e93\">\n                     \n Server Configuration\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nek1665702923991__p_d46388e1_d46389e1_d46390e1\">Memory problems can occur in situations where a separate server process is started for each client process, and the Uniface Router is running in shared mode.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nek1665702923991__p_d46394e1_d46395e1_d46396e1\">You can make server configuration more flexible by using separate assignment files, for example, <span class=\"ph filepath\">database.asn</span> for the DBMS server, <span class=\"ph filepath\">sasv.asn</span> for the application server, and <span class=\"ph filepath\">env.asn</span> for the overall environment.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530226\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530226\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Freeing Memory Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Freeing Memory You can use memory efficiently by using appropriate component implementation techniques and configuring the application and servers appropriately. Using handles allows Uniface to help with automatic garbage collection. Component Implementation When constructing components, consider the following: Drop forms from memory as soon as they are no longer required Delete instances of services that are no longer needed Use limited forms with their reduced field lists Clear entities as soon as the hitlist is no longer needed Free cursors and locks as soon as they are no longer required For more information, see Performance Guidelines for Component Logic and Implementation . Server Configuration Memory problems can occur in situations where a separate server process is started for each client process, and the Uniface Router is running in shared mode. You can make server configuration more flexible by using separate assignment files, for example, database.asn for the DBMS server, sasv.asn for the application server, and env.asn for the overall environment. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}